  "prompt": "Do I have to shave during a passport appointment?",
  "response": "There is no requirement to shave for a passport appointment. When taking your passport photo, the primary concern is that the photo accurately represents your current appearance. As long as your face is clearly visible and meets the guidelines provided by the passport office (such as having a neutral expression, facing forward, and having a plain background), facial hair is generally not an issue. If you have any specific concerns, it's always a good idea to check the photo requirements of the issuing authority or contact them directly for confirmation.",
